name: Ranch Taco Soup
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: This thick and hearty taco soup comes together in a flash. The subtle hint of ranch sets it apart from your average taco soup. Garnish with chopped cilantro if desired.
ingredients: 1 (15 ounce) can whole kernel corn, drained
1 (15 ounce) can black beans, rinsed and drained
1 (10 ounce) can diced tomatoes and green chiles (such as RO*TEL®)
1 (3.8 ounce) can sliced black olives, drained
2 tablespoons ranch dressing mix (such as Hidden Valley Ranch®)
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, and jalapeno in a 4-quart soup pot and cook over medium-high heat until beef is cooked through and no longer pink, about 5 minutes
Add crushed tomatoes, pinto beans, water, corn, black beans, diced tomatoes and green chiles, black olives, ranch dressing, and
Bring soup to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer for 30 minutes
